2.10	Doppelg%C3%A4ngland	Doppelgangland	"Doppelgangland" is the sixteenth episode of the third season of the fantasy television series Buffy the Vampire Slayer (1997–2003). It was written and directed by the show's creator, Joss Whedon, and originally aired on The WB Television Network in the United States on February 23, 1999. The episode's title is derived from the term "Doppelgänger", a German word for a look-alike or double of a living person.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/9c/Buffy_3x16.jpg
